H.P. 1096 - L.D. 1655
An Act to Allow the Keeping of Chickens on Private Residential Property
Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
Sec. 1. 7 MRSA ยง219-D is enacted to read:
ยง219-D. Keeping chickens on residential property
A county or municipality may not adopt a regulation or ordinance that prohibits a
person from keeping chickens on that person's residential property. For purposes of this
section, "chicken" means a female domesticated bird that is raised for meat or eggs and
does not include a fully mature domesticated male chicken. This section may not be
construed to limit the home rule authority of a municipality.
